# Trivy CVE suppression file.
#
# Each line is one CVE id. Trivy excludes these from the report, so they will NOT
# fail the build. Use sparingly and ALWAYS document why a CVE is suppressed.
#
# Format:
#   CVE-YYYY-NNNNN  # Reason for suppression. Expiration: YYYY-MM-DD.
#
# Example:
#   CVE-2024-12345  # False positive in eclipse-temurin alpine layer. Re-evaluate 2026-12-01.
#
# Anything CRITICAL/HIGH that Trivy finds is blocking by default unless listed below.

# spring-security-web: security policy bypass / information disclosure.
# Fixed only in 6.5.9 / 7.0.4, which ship with Spring Boot 3.5.x / 4.0.x. The project
# is pinned to the 3.4.x line (spring-security 6.4.13), so no patched version is available
# without a major-line upgrade. Risk accepted in the interim: the affected matching logic
# is not reachable from our authorization rules (no mvcMatchers ambiguity / servlet-path
# remapping in use). Revisit when bumping to Spring Boot 3.5.x. Expiration: 2026-09-01.
CVE-2026-22732
